<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-155-228  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 155 228.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 13 1989 v10 n11 p66(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Amstrad exec outlines strategy to up sales. (Amstrad CEO VernonMoore)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kellner, Mark A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Vernon Moore, CEO of the Amstrad PLC's US division, says that hisfirm intends to make a major assault on the US microcomputermarket.andP;  Amstrad's strategy will be three-fold: serving thehome-office market through upscale retailers, serving thegovernment and direct mail programs through a special marketdivision, and a major promotion of more sophisticated and powerfulsystems through established computer dealers.andP;  Amstrad currentlyoffers only an 8086-based microcomputer, but the company intendsto introduce new machines before the spring 1989 COMDEX tradeshow.andP;  Amstrad is a member of the Extended Industry StandardArchitecture (EISA) consortium, but also has a licensing agreementwith IBM for the Micro Channel Architecture bus.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Amstrad Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyGoals and ObjectivesPromotion of ProductMicrocomputersManufacturersMarket PenetrationChief Executive Officers.andO;Person:    Moore, Vernon (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>